Class SalesmanagementRestServiceTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.assertj.core.api.Assertions

  • @SpringApplicationConfiguration(classes={io.oasp.gastronomy.restaurant.SpringBootApp.class,SalesmanagementRestTestConfig.class})
@TestPropertySource(properties="flyway.locations=filesystem:src/test/resources/db/tablemanagement")
public class SalesmanagementRestServiceTest
extends AbstractRestServiceTest
    This class serves as an example of how to perform a subsystem test (e.g., call a *RestService interface). The test database is accessed via an instance of the class SalesmanagementRestService.

      • clean

        public void clean()

      • findOrder

        public void findOrder()
        This test method creates a sample instance of OrderCto and saves it into the database. Thereafter the OrderEto object linked to the sample object of OrderCto is loaded from the database and its attributes are tested for correctness.

      • findAllOrders

        public void findAllOrders()
        This test method creates some sample instances of OrderCto and saves them into the database. Thereafter all OrderCto objects are loaded from the database. The method tests the number of loaded OrderCto and the attributes of the sample instances for correctness.

      • findOrderByPost

        public void findOrderByPost()
        This test method creates a sample instance of OrderCto and saves it into the database. Subsequently OrderSearchCriteriaTo like tableId and OrderState are defined. Thereafter the sample OrderCto object is loaded from the database, if its attributes match the OrderSearchCriteriaTo. Finally the attributes of the sample instance of OrderCto are tested for correctness.

      • findOrderPosition

        public void findOrderPosition()
        This test method creates a sample instance of OrderCto and saves it into the database. In addition a sample instance of OrderPositionEto is created, linked to the sample OrderCto object by the id/orderId and saved into the database. Finally a the sample instance of OrderPositionEto is identified by its id, loaded from the database and its attributes are tested for correctness.

      • findAllOrderPositions

        public void findAllOrderPositions()
        This test method creates a sample instance of OrderCto and saves it into the database. In addition some sample instances of OrderPositionEto are created, linked to sampleOrderCto by the id/orderId and saved into the database. Thereafter all OrderPositionEto objects are loaded from the database. The method tests the number of loaded orderPositionEtos and the attributes of the sample instances for correctness.

      • cancelOrderPosition

        public void cancelOrderPosition()
        This test method creates a sample instance of OrderCto and saves it into the database. In addition a sample instance of OrderPositionEto is created, linked to the sample OrderCto object by the id/orderId and saved into the database. After that another OrderCto object comprising a OrderEto object with the same id/orderId as the the previously saved OrderCto/OrderEto object is saved into the database. The resulting effect of the all OrderPositionEto objects being cancelled is tested.

      • getNumberOfOrders

        protected int getNumberOfOrders()
        This test method loads all saved OrderCto objects from the database, counts the number and returns it.
        Returns:
        number of orders saved in the database

      • getNumberOfOrderPositions

        protected int getNumberOfOrderPositions()
        This test method loads all saved OrderPositionEto objects from the database, counts the number and returns it.
        Returns:
        number of orderPositions saved in the database
